summary: This is a travel authorization email from the Department of Justice's E2 travel system, approving travel for an FBI agent to conduct a witness interview in Beverly Hills, CA as part of the Epstein investigation. The travel is scheduled for February 25-29, 2020, and is pending final authorization.

events.title: Scheduled Witness Interview in Beverly Hills
events.description: Planned travel for an FBI agent to conduct a witness interview in Beverly Hills, CA as part of the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The Department of Justice was actively conducting witness interviews in the Epstein investigation as of February 2020.
Travel was authorized for an FBI agent to Beverly Hills, CA from February 25-29, 2020 for a witness interview.
The travel authorization reference number was 11063602 and the trip ID was R20NYS13404.
The document shows the DOJ's internal travel approval process for investigation-related activities.
